WEBVTT

00:00.300 --> 00:03.934
Quorum — the Nonprofit Board OS.

00:04.234 --> 00:13.556
Welcome back. In this video, we'll sign in to the portal — and put it on your phone or
computer, so it's always one tap away.

00:13.856 --> 00:20.610
Start at your organization's web address. This page is your board's private front door.

00:20.910 --> 00:30.400
Click the first box, and type your username. It's usually your first name, or your name
with a dot — you'll find it in your welcome email.

00:30.700 --> 00:40.454
Next, click the Password box, and type your password. If you ever forget it, use the
Forgot link on the right — no shame in it.

00:40.754 --> 00:50.100
Leave "Keep me signed in" checked on your own device. Then click the big Sign in button.
And just like that — you're home.

00:50.400 --> 00:57.802
One more nice touch. In the bottom corner of the menu, find Install app — and click it.

00:58.102 --> 01:08.024
Follow the short steps you see. On a phone, it's "Add to Home Screen." The portal
becomes an app icon — no app store needed.

01:08.324 --> 01:16.662
From then on, Quorum opens full screen, straight from your home screen. One tap, and
you're at the board's door.

01:16.962 --> 01:22.756
That's it. Next, let's take a proper look around your Dashboard.
